A cron-like expression, extending the usual UN*X definition to include_triggers on the second as well as minute, hour, day of month, month_and day of week. e.g. "0 * * * * MON-FRI" means once_per minute on weekdays (at the top of the minute - the 0th second)._@return an expression that can be parsed to a cron schedule

A cron-like expression, extending the usual UN*X definition to include_triggers on the second as well as minute, hour, day of month, month_and day of week.  e.g. {@code "0 * * * * MON-FRI"} means once per minute on_weekdays (at the top of the minute - the 0th second)._@return an expression that can be parsed to a cron schedule_@see org.springframework.scheduling.support.CronSequenceGenerator

A cron-like expression, extending the usual UN*X definition to include triggers_on the second as well as minute, hour, day of month, month and day of week._

E.g. {@code "0 * * * * MON-FRI"} means once per minute on weekdays_(at the top of the minute - the 0th second)._

The special value {@link #CRON_DISABLED "-"} indicates a disabled cron trigger,_primarily meant for externally specified values resolved by a ${...} placeholder._@return an expression that can be parsed to a cron schedule_@see org.springframework.scheduling.support.CronSequenceGenerator
